OL,3,CWhat is Badenochism?
OL,5,FTo be clear, even Badenoch's and
OL,6,FStride's fiscal prudence has its
OL,7,Fpolitical limits: neither is
OL,8,Fsuggesting reforms or cuts to the
OL,9,Fbiggest long-term contributor to the
OL,10,Fballooning public spending, namely the
OL,11,Frising cost of pensions and support
OL,12,Ffor the elderly. The calculation is
OL,13,Fpresumably that a Tory party without
OL,14,Fany retired voters is literally one
OL,15,Fleader and her dog.
OL,17,FBut are British voters ready for
OL,18,FBadenoch's hair-shirtism as millions
OL,19,Fstruggle to pay for their shopping or
OL,20,Fsecure a hospital appointment?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
